programme.desc: Guo Jing and Huang Rong go to Iron Palm Peak to search for the Book of Wumu. The chief of Iron Palm discovers their visit, and seriously injures Huang.

programme.title: Shaolin Abbot
programme.desc: The Monk Chi San (David Chiang) is sent by his Shaolin masters to learn a special kung fu from a Wu-Tang priest and befriends his niece Wu Mei (Lily Li).

programme.title: The Mad Monk Strikes Again
programme.desc: The Mad Monk is up against the equally legendary scholar-turned-genie, Lu Tung Pin. The duo create havoc as they vie with each other, be it in mirth, magic, women or weapons!

programme.title: Crippled Avengers
programme.desc: Chang Cheh follows his international hit, The Five Venoms with a popular sequel about blind, deaf, footless and child-like kung-fu fighters who brilliantly train to take their revenge.

programme.title: Hex After Hex
programme.desc: Beloved cult director Kueh Chih Hung delivers this deranged romantic tragedy centring on muscular demon Lo Meng, whose attempts to possess the soul of his true love backfire.

programme.title: King Gambler
programme.desc: A pre-cursor to the gambling craze that swept Asian Cinema, here cardsharp is pitted against cardsharp in a kung-fu fuelled duel of fists and wits to become king of the casino.

programme.title: The Younger Generation
programme.desc: This is a tragic tale about a young girl, played by Ivy Ling Po, who gets married and has five kids. She and her husband later die, forcing one child to be sold into prostitution to feed the other four.

programme.title: Monkey Kung Fu
programme.desc: Wei Chun is a cocky young man sentenced to jail for killing a man in a fight. One day, Wei Chun picks a fight with an old man that turns out to be the master of monkey style kung fu and as they become friends.

programme.title: The Warlord
programme.desc: A bandit became a warlord in the northern China by helping Russia fight against Japan. The warlord was finally killed by the daughter of a troupe master whom he had killed for no reason.

programme.title: New One-Armed Swordsman
programme.desc: David Chiang leaps into action as all-new one-armed hero when the love of his life is kidnapped and his best friend is murdered by a gang hiding out on Tiger Mountain.

programme.title: Gossip Street
programme.desc: The place to be is flat number 8 on the second floor of the Gossip Street apartment building, where neighbors gather to gossip. The sitcom turns serious when a local mobster wants to change the place into a gambling den.

programme.title: The Thunderbolt Fist
programme.desc: Just after the Chinese Revolution, Japanese invaders start to infiltrate Northeast China. In the film, a vicious judo expert Arashi Tani wants to prove that Chinese are the sick people of Asia.

programme.title: Two Con Men
programme.desc: A wonderfully twisted, pseudo-romantic comedy starring Liang Tien and Chang Ying in an age-old competition between rookie con artist versus the ultimate, experienced flimflam man.

programme.title: Magnificent Wanderers
programme.desc: Lin and his two friends are traveling patriots who vow to stand up against violence and fight for justice. They meet a rich young man Chu by chance one day and the four become best friends.

programme.title: The Venus' Tear Diamond
programme.desc: Legendary rival jewel thieves Fragrant Night and Nocturnal Earl travel to Japan to steal the famous Venus' Tear Diamond.

programme.title: Ghosts Galore
programme.desc: Young Taoist priest Lu and his friend are nearly killed by a female ghost during an exorcism. Luckily, Master Lian saves their lives, so they beseech him to teach them his skills.

programme.title: Men From The Monastery
programme.desc: The disciples of the Shaolin Monastery are soon fighting alongside the patriots in their fierce struggle against the invaders, and the fate of a nation lies in the lethal hands of the Men From The Monastery.

programme.title: The Dream Of The Red Chamber
programme.desc: The fruitless love between Bao Yu and Dai Yu. The marriage of this beloved couple seems next to impossible, as the ruthless mother of Bao Yu deliberately arranges the marriage of his son with another lady.

programme.title: The Imperial Tomb Raiders
programme.desc: The story revolves around a maverick, a band of woman warriors and a group of ruthless bandits. The maverick teams up with the woman warriors to battle the bandits seeking to raid the emperor's tomb.

programme.title: Inside The Forbidden City
programme.desc: Justice Bao discovers that Consort Li's new born son was swapped at birth and that she was expelled from the palace by Empress Liu twenty years ago. He sets Eunuch Guo up to confess his conspiracy with the Empress.

programme.title: The Spiritual Boxer
programme.desc: Wang Yu is a fake ghost catcher whose deficient skills make him ill-equipped to fend off the irritable townsfolk. When he doublecrosses a local gangster, he is forced to fight.

programme.title: The House Of 72 Tenants
programme.desc: The 72 inhabitants of a dilapidated tenement live under the thumb of a heartless landlady and her sleazy husband. The arrival of a defiant new tenant however, changes their fate.

programme.title: The Rescue
programme.desc: A group of Song survivors band together to save their prime minister from the encroaching Yuan forces. However, two heroes are imprisoned and must either escape or lose their lives!

programme.title: The Grand Substitution
programme.desc: This Huangmei Opera epic stars Li Li-hua and Ivy Ling Po in the story of a loyal Imperial Court servant who gives up his own newborn son to save the prince from an evil official.

programme.title: The Lizard
programme.desc: A master thief earned his nickname 'The Lizard' by gliding on walls. Together with his partner, they ran against a corrupt police chief.

programme.title: Diau Charn
programme.desc: Set in the Han Dynasty, a gang of loyalists led by Yang Chi-ching and Lin Dai, strive to drive a wedge between the governor and his son, eventually turning them against each other.

programme.title: Lady With A Sword
programme.desc: Kao Pao-shu shows that women can successfully direct a heroic bloodshed film, casting Shaw's darling Lily Ho as the embittered woman searching for the man who murdered her sister.

programme.title: Emperor Chien Lung And Beauty
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung meets a famous courtesan in Suzhou and in order to spend as much time as possible with her, he builds a direct underground tunnel into the Forbidden City.

programme.title: The Singing Thief
programme.desc: Legendary martial arts director Chang Cheh tries his hand at the musical, with Taiwanese songstress Lin Chong on board as a cool jewel thief who reforms to become a club singer.

programme.title: Enchanting Shadow
programme.desc: A young scholar spends the night in a creepy temple that is said to be haunted. He doesn't believe in the rumors, but after running into a Taoist swordsman, he meets a beautiful lady ghost.

programme.title: The Delinquent
programme.desc: This film is a coming-of-age tale of the lower-class Hong Kong teens in the 1960s. Wang is the title character, a hotheaded and rebellious teen who is tempted by the dark side.

programme.title: The Sword Of Swords
programme.desc: The Sword Master passes on his sword to his disciple Lin before he dies. Another disciple Fang also eyes the sword and plots to take it away from Lin, destroying his family and blinding him in the process.

programme.title: Scandal
programme.desc: As the roguish scamp Zhen and his best friend Chia collected proofs of corruption from the officials, they demanded to become the governor of the country.

programme.title: The Brave Archer 2
programme.desc: Knowing Guo Jing has won Huang Rong's hand in marriage using the kung fu learned from Jiu Yin manual, Ouyang Feng captures Huang and agrees to release her only if Guo can dictate the content of the manual.

programme.title: Asia-Pol
programme.desc: Asiapol agent Yang Ming Xuan trails a shipment of contraband gold being delivered to gang leader, George Eaton. He enlists the help of a Chinese woman who is trying to avenge her sister.

programme.title: Gambler's Delight
programme.desc: Danny Lee is a desperate gambler, who cheats his way into running a Macau casino, only to face off against a Japanese gang leader in his precursor to the 80s gambling movie craze.

programme.title: The Pearl Phoenix
programme.desc: In Huangmei Opera tradition, this movie tells the love story of Wen, who sells himself as a slave to a rich family, and Huo, the family's young daughter.

programme.title: Heroes Two
programme.desc: Shaolin student Chen is badly wounded by the Qing army, and the young Fu hands him to the evil general by mistake. Now the two heroes must settle the score with the general.

programme.title: Sweet And Wild
programme.desc: Hsiao Fang is a young girl not afraid to fight back against hooligans. Unfortunately, she mistakes the handsome Ma Ta-hai, for one such hoodlum. The two are immediately attracted but refuse to admit their true feelings.

programme.title: Angel With The Iron Fists
